{"ts": "2026-04-03T23:57:48.398", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "f66740e6-58fe-4eca-a98a-1e60ae2dfd93", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/f66740e6-58fe-4eca-a98a-1e60ae2dfd93.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Read", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/config/paths.py"}, "tool_response": {"type": "text", "file": {"filePath": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/config/paths.py", "content": "\"\"\"paths.py \u2014 Canonical path constants for the workflow system.\"\"\"\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nWORKFLOW_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent\n\nDEFAULT_STATE_PATH = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"state.json\"\nLOG_FILE = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"workflow.log\"\nDEBUG_LOG_FILE = Path(\"DEBUG.log\")\n", "numLines": 10, "startLine": 1, "totalLines": 10}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01RMCFqggGU1jXM7jq7SvJwd"}}
{"ts": "2026-04-03T23:57:48.456", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "f66740e6-58fe-4eca-a98a-1e60ae2dfd93", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/f66740e6-58fe-4eca-a98a-1e60ae2dfd93.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Read", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/lib/file_manager.py"}, "tool_response": {"type": "text", "file": {"filePath": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/hooks/workflow/lib/file_manager.py", "content": "\"\"\"FileManager with file locking for JSON/JSONL files.\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Callable, cast, Literal\nfrom filelock import FileLock, BaseFileLock\nimport sys\n\nJSON_SUFFIXES = {\".json\", \".jsonl\"}\n\n\ndef create_file(path: Path, default: Any | None = None) -> None:\n    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    if path.suffix == \".json\":\n        default = default or {}\n        path.write_text(json.dumps(default, indent=2), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n        return\n    path.touch()\n\n\ndef load_file(path: Path) -> Any:\n    if not path.exists():\n        create_file(path)\n    try:\n        content = path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\").strip()\n        if not content:\n            return {}\n\n        return json.loads(content)\n\n    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Corrupt JSON in {path}: {e}\") from e\n\n\ndef save_file(data: Any, mode: Literal[\"w\", \"a\", \"x\"], path: Path) -> None:\n    try:\n        with path.open(mode, encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            if path.suffix in JSON_SUFFIXES:\n                json.dump(data, f, indent=2)\n            else:\n                f.write(data)\n    except TypeError as e:\n        raise TypeError(f\"Invalid data type: {type(data)} \\nError: {e}\") from e\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Error saving file: {path} \\nError: {e}\") from e\n\n\ndef update_file(path: Path, fn: Callable[[Any], None]) -> None:\n    data = load_file(path)\n    fn(data)\n    save_file(data, \"w\", path)\n\n\nclass FileManager:\n    def __init__(self, path: Path, lock: bool = True):\n        self._path = path\n        self._lock = FileLock(path.with_suffix(\".lock\")) if lock else None\n\n    def create_file(self, default: Any | None = None) -> None:\n        create_file(self._path, default)\n\n    def load_file(self) -> Any:\n        if self._lock is None:\n            return load_file(self._path)\n        with self._lock:\n            return load_file(self._path)\n\n    def save_file(self, data: Any, mode: Literal[\"w\", \"a\", \"x\"] = \"w\") -> None:\n        save_file(data, mode, self._path)\n\n    def update_file(self, fn: Callable[[Any], None]) -> None:\n        data = load_file(self._path)\n        fn(data)\n        save_file(data, \"w\", self._path)\n\n    def delete_file(self) -> None:\n        self._path.unlink()\n", "numLines": 79, "startLine": 1, "totalLines": 79}}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01MXPETxNJPDWxqfxLNRnLZQ"}}
{"ts": "2026-04-03T23:58:13.757", "event": "PostToolUse:raw_input", "raw_input": {"session_id": "f66740e6-58fe-4eca-a98a-1e60ae2dfd93", "transcript_path": "/home/emhar/.claude/projects/-home-emhar-avaris-ai/f66740e6-58fe-4eca-a98a-1e60ae2dfd93.jsonl", "cwd": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai", "permission_mode": "plan", "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "tool_name": "Write", "tool_input": {"file_path": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/plans/deep-cuddling-island.md", "content": "# Plan: Async Auto-Commit Hook on TaskCompleted\n\n## Context\n\nThe user wants an async hook that fires after each `TaskCompleted` event. It should detect dirty files via `git status`, batch them into a state file, invoke headless Claude (`claude --bare -p`) to generate a commit message, then commit the files \u2014 all without blocking the main session.\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n| File | Action | Purpose |\n|------|--------|---------|\n| `.claude/hooks/workflow/auto_commit.py` | **Create** | Main async hook script |\n| `.claude/hooks/workflow/config/paths.py` | **Modify** | Add `COMMIT_BATCH_PATH` constant |\n| `.claude/hooks/workflow/config/__init__.py` | **Modify** | Export new constant |\n| `.claude/settings.local.json` | **Modify** | Register async hook alongside existing sync hook |\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Step 1: Add path constant\n\n**`.claude/hooks/workflow/config/paths.py`** \u2014 Add:\n```python\nCOMMIT_BATCH_PATH = WORKFLOW_ROOT / \"commit_batch.json\"\n```\n\n**`.claude/hooks/workflow/config/__init__.py`** \u2014 Add `COMMIT_BATCH_PATH` to the imports from `workflow.config.paths`.\n\n### Step 2: Create `auto_commit.py`\n\n**`.claude/hooks/workflow/auto_commit.py`** \u2014 New file, executable (`chmod +x`).\n\nFlow:\n1. Read stdin JSON (gets `task_subject`, `task_id`, etc.)\n2. Use `StateStore` on `commit_batch.json` for batch state (reuses existing file-locking pattern via `FileManager`)\n3. Run `git status --porcelain` to find dirty files\n4. Filter out excluded patterns (state.json, *.pyc, __pycache__, lock files, logs, settings.local.json)\n5. If no files \u2192 log skip, exit\n6. Save file list + task_subject to `commit_batch.json`\n7. Run `claude --bare -p \"<prompt>\"` to generate commit message (no tools needed, pure text gen)\n8. Run `git add <files>` + `git commit -m \"<message>\"`\n9. Update batch status to \"committed\"\n10. Log success, output `systemMessage` for next-turn delivery\n\nKey design decisions:\n- **`--bare` flag** on headless Claude prevents recursive hook triggers (essential!)\n- **`StateStore`/`FileManager`** on `commit_batch.json` provides file locking (`.lock` sibling) \u2014 prevents concurrent auto-commits from racing\n- **Lock timeout of 10s** \u2014 if another instance is running, give up gracefully\n- **Fallback commit message** if headless Claude fails: `\"chore: auto-commit after task ({task_subject})\"`\n- **Exclude patterns**: `state.json`, `*.pyc`, `__pycache__/`, `commit_batch.json`, `workflow.log`, `locks/`, `settings.local.json`\n\n### Step 3: Register async hook in settings\n\n**`.claude/settings.local.json`** \u2014 Add second entry to `TaskCompleted` array:\n\n```json\n\"TaskCompleted\": [\n  {\n    \"hooks\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"\\\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\\\"/.claude/hooks/workflow/dispatchers/task_completed.py\",\n        \"timeout\": 30\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"hooks\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"\\\"$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR\\\"/.claude/hooks/workflow/auto_commit.py\",\n        \"timeout\": 120,\n        \"async\": true\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n]\n```\n\n- `timeout: 120` \u2014 headless Claude can take 30-60s, plus git ops\n- `async: true` \u2014 non-blocking, output delivered next turn\n\n## Execution Flow\n\n```\nTaskCompleted fires\n  |\n  +---> [sync] task_completed.py (existing guardrail \u2014 blocks or allows)\n  |\n  +---> [async] auto_commit.py (new, non-blocking)\n            |\n            +-- Read stdin JSON\n            +-- Acquire file lock (commit_batch.lock via StateStore)\n            +-- git status --porcelain \u2192 filter excluded patterns\n            +-- If no files: log skip, exit\n            +-- Save batch to commit_batch.json\n            +-- claude --bare -p \"generate commit message for: ...\"\n            +-- git add <files> && git commit -m \"<message>\"\n            +-- Update batch status, log success\n            +-- Output systemMessage \u2192 delivered next turn\n```\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n1. **No dirty files** \u2192 skip, log, exit\n2. **Headless Claude fails** \u2192 fallback to template message `chore: auto-commit after task (subject)`\n3. **Concurrent firings** \u2192 file lock prevents racing; second instance logs timeout and exits\n4. **Git commit fails** \u2192 catch CalledProcessError, log, exit (async hooks can't block anyway)\n5. **Recursive prevention** \u2192 `--bare` flag ensures headless Claude never loads hooks\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Make a file change, trigger TaskCompleted manually:\n   ```bash\n   echo '{\"hook_event_name\":\"TaskCompleted\",\"task_id\":\"test-1\",\"task_subject\":\"Test task\",\"session_id\":\"test\",\"cwd\":\"/home/emhar/avaris-ai\"}' | python3 .claude/hooks/workflow/auto_commit.py\n   ```\n2. Check `git log -1` to verify commit was created with a sensible message\n3. Check `commit_batch.json` shows status \"committed\"\n4. Check `workflow.log` for AutoCommit log entries\n5. Verify no recursive hooks by checking only one commit was made\n"}, "tool_response": {"type": "create", "filePath": "/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/plans/deep-cuddling-island.md", "content": "# Plan: Async Auto-Commit Hook on TaskCompleted\n\n## Context\n\nThe user wants an async hook that fires after each `TaskCompleted` event. It should detect dirty files via `git status`, batch them into a state file, invoke headless Claude (`claude --bare -p`) to generate a commit message, then commit the files \u2014 all without blocking the m